Looksmaxxing tip:

Lots of people will tell you to be as lean as possible for a good looking face, but this is not always right. Some people's faces look better at a slightly higher bodyfat %.

Something I have been doing a lot lately are single-hand dumbbell overhead carries. Just pick a dumbbell and hold it over your hand, then walk around. Trains your stability, also quite functional.

Supplement: Brewer's yeast, natural (not pill form). Contains lots of stuff, more importantly magnesium and zinc, tastes nicely and can be used as a spice for soup or ayran. Works well for weight gain, it is an older trick used by soviet boxing coaches for younger skinny athletes

The most important thing the Church can do, to remain relevant in modern worldly life as an institution, is to heavily encourage spontaneous, illogical, uncalculated, potentially disastrous and life-ruining, lacking clear future, risky marriages between very young people.

Youth is best represented as passion, risk, feeling. Modernity ruins marriage by pushing it to the more mature late 20s or 30s, making a mockery of it, making it safe, boring, calculated - an abomination. Make people marry when they're 19 and let them figure it all out together.

Young people are fire; and fire can not be changed, only extinguished. Do we really want to make people wait until they are 26, with a stable job and a house, to experience love? Why do we think marriage is a finishing touch of a life when it should be a grounding stone?
